        <Commentary>
            <ab>Y2.4b <em>frādat̰.fšaōm</em>] Geldner, Kellens <em>frādat̰.fšāum</em>. Mss. mostly <em>frādat̰.fšaō/om</em>. Only 500, 510 <em>frādat̰.fšāum</em>. 
                Cf. ending <em>-aūm</em>, well preserved in other attestations: Y1.23, Y10.4 <em>aṣ̌āum</em> or Y9.22 <em>arənāum</em>. 
                Vid. <bibl>Kuiper, 1942</bibl>, p. 52 considers it an actual hysterodynamic;  also <bibl>Tremblay, 2003</bibl>, pp. 248 ff. from a different stem than <em>frādat̰.fšauue</em> (Y1.4): 
                <em>frādat̰.fšu-</em> as noun (dat. <em>frādat̰.fšauue</em>), <em>frādat̰.fšaō-</em> as a derivative of the first (acc. <em>frādat̰.fšaōm</em>).</ab>
        </Commentary>
